
[1]speaker

   SPE'AKER, n.

   1. One that speaks, in what ever manner.

   2. One that proclaims or celebrates. -No other speaker of my living
   actions.

   3. One that utters or pronounces a discourse; usually, one that utters
   a speech in public. We say, a man is a good speaker, or a bad speaker.

   4. The person who presides in a deliberative assembly, preserving order
   and regulating the debates; as the speaker of the house of commons; the
   speaker of a house or representatives.
